  "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nThe `sszAllForksLightClient` namespace export in `@lodestar/types` cannot be indexed by a value of type `ForkName` since `sszAllForksLightClient` does not include `phase0` so Typescript complains.  \n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI should be able to use a value of type `ForkName` (or some alternative like LightClientForkName) as an index type `allForksLightClient` namespace.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `git clone https://github.com/ethereumjs/ultralight.git`\r\n2. `npm i` from the repo root\r\n3. `cd packages/cli`\r\n4. `npx ts-node-esm scripts/bootstrapFinder.ts`\n\n### Additional context\n\nProduces errors like below\r\n![image](https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/assets/17355484/cd7d9b53-8a9c-4243-b451-ebbc8e9d4b3e)\r\n\r\nI have to use `//@ts-ignore` in places like [this](https://github.com/ethereumjs/ultralight/blob/d2a2cb48d6526babc9f8a80b8c8c12957786f398/packages/cli/scripts/bootstrapFinder.ts#L37) in order to use the `ForkName` value provided from some Light Client data structure provided by the lodestar API when using the `sszAllForksLightClientSSZTypes` namespace.\n\n### Operating system\n\nLinux\n\n### Lodestar version or commit hash\n\nLodestar version 1.11.0",
